The paper deals with real-time image recognition, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves probabilistic densities and likelihoods, which are concepts commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of histograms of oriented gradients and deep neural network-based image features, which are common techniques in image retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
